Do's

*Keep your profiles on a privacy setting and regularly review who can see your posts.
*Think before you post — ask yourself if you'd be comfortable with a professor or future employer seeing it.
*Give proper credit when sharing someone else's work, photos, or ideas.
*Use social media to build a positive personal brand — share achievements, projects, and learning.
*Verify information before sharing — check the source and cross-reference with credible outlets.



Don'ts

*Don't share your location, address, phone number, or daily routine publicly.
*Don't post or share content in anger or frustration — always pause and reflect first.
*Don't plagiarise or repost others' content without attribution or permission.
*Don't engage in or encourage cyberbullying, trolling, or online harassment of any kind.
*Don't spread unverified news, rumours, or misinformation, even if it seems believable.
